<figureCitation id="13292A67FFA0FF85E1F722C2BA98FF2F" box="[159,229,186,211]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1848,1870]" captionTargetBox="[262,1339,234,1759]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[209,1367,195,1798]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Adults in dorsal and ventral views. Taxon names appear below each set. Bia decaerulea decaerulea: a, male, Brazil, Amazonas, Manacapuru (CMNH); b, female, same locality (CMNH). Bia decaerulea cayana, Simonsen &amp; Penz, new ssp.: c, male holotype, French Guiana, Mana River (CMNH); d, male paratype, same locality (CMNH); e, male paratype, same locality (CMNH); f, female paratype, French Guiana, Oyapok River (CMNH). Bia decaerulea pallida Casagrande &amp; Penz, new ssp: g, male holotype, Brazil, Amazonas, Barcelos, Rio Padauari (DZUP); h, female paratype, Brazil, Amazonas, Barcelos, Rio Padauari (DZUP)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569733/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Figs 4</figureCitation>
