<subSubSection id="C3086569FFA0FF85E1AF2178BE5DFCC1" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAD36E2FFA0FF85E1AF2178BE5DFCC1" blockId="12.[151,1437,258,829]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">
<emphasis id="B966EAF0FFA0FF85E1AF2178BB46FCE5" bold="true" box="[199,315,768,793]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Remarks.</emphasis>
Some specimens from Guyana and Suriname (Appendix) seem to be intermediate between 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D61FFA0FF85E4552179BFE6FCE4" box="[1341,1435,769,792]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="actorion">
<emphasis id="B966EAF0FFA0FF85E4552179BFE6FCE4" box="[1341,1435,769,792]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">actorion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D61FFA0FF85E1AE215CBB3FFCC0" box="[198,322,804,828]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decaerulea">
<emphasis id="B966EAF0FFA0FF85E1AE215CBB3FFCC0" box="[198,322,804,828]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">decaerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see explanation in 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D61FFA0FF85E34C215DB894FCC0" box="[548,745,805,828]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="actorion" subSpecies="actorion">
<emphasis id="B966EAF0FFA0FF85E34C215DB894FCC0" box="[548,745,805,828]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">actorion actorion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subspecies account above).
</paragraph>
